\title{Definition of an Ultrafilter}
\date{2024-03-01}
\author{gpeters}
\taxon{definition}

\p{Let #{I} be any set. Then an ultrafilter #{\mathcal{U}} on #{\mathcal{P}(I)} is a proper [filter](BMT-d071) on #{I} with the additional property:}
\p{For every #{A\subseteq I}, either #{A\in\mathcal{U}} or #{I\backslash A\in\mathcal{U}}.}
\p{Every proper filter can be extended into an ultrafilter.}

